<h2 style="margin:0 0 16px;font-size:20px;font-weight:600;color:#111;line-height:1.3;">
  {{ notification.title | e }}
</h2>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  {{ notification.body | e }}
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;padding:14px;background:#fef3c7;border-left:3px solid #f59e0b;font-size:14px;color:#78350f;line-height:1.5;">
  <strong>Security note:</strong> a new MCP API key grants full
  programmatic access to your organization's cameras, nodes, and
  incident data.  Anyone holding this key can list cameras, view
  live frames via <code>view_camera</code>, and file incidents on
  the org's behalf.
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 8px;font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;font-weight:600;">
  If YOU created this key intentionally
</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  No action needed.  This email is the audit-trail companion to the
  key generation.
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 8px;font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;font-weight:600;">
  If you DIDN'T create this key
</p>
<ol style="margin:0 0 24px;padding-left:20px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;color:#374151;">
  <li>Open the MCP settings page (link below)</li>
  <li>Find the new key in the list</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Revoke</strong> on it immediately</li>
  <li>Audit recent MCP activity at <code style="background:#f3f4f6;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;font-family:ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace;font-size:13px;">/admin/mcp</code></li>
</ol>

<table role="presentation" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
  <tr>
    <td style="background:#22c55e;border-radius:6px;">
      <a href="{{ dashboard_url }}/mcp"
         style="display:inline-block;padding:10px 18px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0a0a0f;text-decoration:none;">
        Manage MCP keys →
      </a>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:24px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.5;">
  This alert went only to organization admins.
</p>
